to the editor i was saddened to come face to page with the reality that our media are cutting back on coverage of the sept 11 anniversary citing the sense that many people would prefer not to spend much time in reflection this year recalling sept 11 quietly business day sept 1 i hardly think that what we need is to engage only in national analysis and not national mourning i feel the need to watch this year 's ceremony to mourn for an america that turns away from feeling and that does n't deal with the reality of the problems we face about which we can no longer claim innocence i feel the need to reflect on the changes that sept 11 has wrought in the families and friends and colleagues of the dead in the survivors and their families friends and colleagues and in the rest of us here and elsewhere at our common address planet earth estelle haferling new york sept 1 2003

